'''August Adler''' (24 January 1863, [[Opava]], [[Austrian Silesia]] – 17 October 1923, [[Vienna]]) was a [[Czechs|Czech]] and [[Austrians|Austrian]] [[mathematician]] noted for using the theory of [[inversive geometry|inversion]] to provide an alternate proof of [[Mascheroni]]'s [[compass and straightedge]] construction theorem.

