{{distinguish|Florodora}}

'''"Floradora"''', also called '''Keyword,''' was a doubly [[Cipher|enciphered]] diplomatic [[Code (cryptography)|code]] used by the Germans during the [[Second World War]].  The Allies used  [[Unit record equipment|tabulating equipment]], created by [[IBM]], to break the code over period of more than a year in 1941 and 1942.

